tissueExpression.summary: A majority of normal tissues displayed cytoplasmic staining with a granular pattern, often of moderate to strong intensity. Strongest staining was observed in glial cells, hepatocytes and exocrine glandular cells. Mucus-producing cells stained distinctly.

Partly consistent with extensive gene/protein characterization data

image.description: Immunohistochemical staining of human kidney shows strong granular cytoplasmic positivity in cells in tubules.

tissueExpression.summary: Moderate to strong cytoplasmic staining with a granular pattern was observed in some hepatocellular carcinomas, malignant gliomas and prostate cancers. Most other tumors were weakly stained or negative.
